<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="231" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,386,1095]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Petrunkevitch" authorityYear="1910" box="[199,473,458,483]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculatus">
<emphasis box="[199,473,458,483]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadinus tuberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was based on a holotype female from Poço Grande (Fazenda Poço Grande, Juquiá, São Paulo, Brazil). The description and illustration of the holotype shows a specimen of large size (longer than 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
) that lacks the diagnostic needle-shaped setae of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon, 1895:" authorityYear="1052" box="[747,873,530,555]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[747,873,530,555]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, indicating that this species does not belong to the genus. The analysis of the photos of the holotype (
<figureCitation box="[735,879,566,591]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[330,1266,1150,1961]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[330,1266,1150,1961]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 14. Epicadus pustulosus (Mello-Leitão, 1929), subadult female holotype [total length: 10.5 mm]. A–D habitus (A dorsal, B ventral, C frontal, D lateral). Photo credits: R. Pupedis and PMNH Laboratory of Arachnology crew." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458516/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Figs 14A–D</figureCitation>
), sent by the curator of the Peabody Museum of Natural History, allows us to recognize that the holotype is in fact an immature female with only the primordium of the epigynum. This species clearly belongs to a group of species that 
<bibRefCitation box="[956,1212,638,663]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24408" refString="Machado, M., Teixeira, R. A. &amp; Lise, A. A. (2017) Cladistic analysis supports the monophyly of the Neotropical crab spider genus Epicadus and its senior synonymy over Tobias (Araneae: Thomisidae). Invertebrate Systematics, 31, 442 - 455. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 16074" type="journal article">
Machado 
<emphasis box="[1069,1128,638,663]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
named “ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[1317,1435,638,663]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pustulosus">
<emphasis box="[1317,1435,638,663]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">pustulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade”, which is composed of spiders with cryptic bark-dweller habitus due to its dark and rough tegument, and by the presence of large pustular setiferous tubercles in femora I and II (composed of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mello-LeitÃ £ o" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[1124,1340,710,735]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudatus">
<emphasis box="[1124,1340,710,735]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadus caudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Mello- 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,304,746,771]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24568" refString="Mello-Leitao, C. F. (1929) Aphantochilidas e Thomisidas do Brasil. Arquivos do Museu Nacional do Rio de Janeiro, 31, 9 - 359." type="journal article">Leitão, 1929</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mello-Leitao, 1929)" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1929" baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[331,827,746,771]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pustulosus">
<emphasis box="[331,568,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadus pustulosus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[591,819,746,771]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24568" refString="Mello-Leitao, C. F. (1929) Aphantochilidas e Thomisidas do Brasil. Arquivos do Museu Nacional do Rio de Janeiro, 31, 9 - 359." type="journal article">Mello-Leitão, 1929</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Banks, 1909" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1909" box="[898,1305,746,771]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulatus">
<emphasis box="[898,1138,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadus granulatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[1153,1305,746,771]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref23652" refString="Banks, N. (1909) Arachnida from Costa Rica. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 61, 194 - 234. Benjamin, S. P. (2011) Phylogenetics and comparative morphology of crab spiders (Araneae: Dionycha, Thomisidae). Zootaxa, 3080, 1 - 108." type="journal article">Banks, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mello-LeitÃ £ o" baseAuthorityYear="1929" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadus caudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on a female holotype from the city of Rio de Janeiro, has been recorded from the state of São Paulo (
<bibRefCitation box="[158,400,818,843]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24345" refString="Machado, M., Teixeira, R. A. &amp; Lise, A. A. (2015) Taxonomic notes on the crab spider genus Tobias Simon, 1895 (Araneae, Thomisidae, Stephanopinae). Zootaxa, 4034 (3), 565 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4034.3.8" type="journal article">
Machado 
<emphasis box="[274,325,818,843]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[414,656,818,843]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24473" refString="Machado, M., Teixeira, R. A. &amp; Lise, A. A. (2018) There and back again: more on the taxonomy of the crab spiders genus Epicadus (Thomisidae: Stephanopinae). Zootaxa, 4382 (3), 501 - 530. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4382.3.4" type="journal article">
Machado 
<emphasis box="[527,579,818,843]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[677,909,818,843]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pustulosus">
<emphasis box="[677,909,818,843]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Epicadus pustulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on an immature female holotype from Fonteboa, Amazonas state, northern Brazil, reaches south to the state of São Paulo (
<bibRefCitation box="[1086,1321,854,879]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24345" refString="Machado, M., Teixeira, R. A. &amp; Lise, A. A. (2015) Taxonomic notes on the crab spider genus Tobias Simon, 1895 (Araneae, Thomisidae, Stephanopinae). Zootaxa, 4034 (3), 565 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4034.3.8" type="journal article">
Machado 
<emphasis box="[1199,1248,854,879]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24473" refString="Machado, M., Teixeira, R. A. &amp; Lise, A. A. (2018) There and back again: more on the taxonomy of the crab spiders genus Epicadus (Thomisidae: Stephanopinae). Zootaxa, 4382 (3), 501 - 530. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4382.3.4" type="journal article">
Machado 
<emphasis box="[151,199,890,915]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). As stated in 
<bibRefCitation box="[431,673,890,915]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24345" refString="Machado, M., Teixeira, R. A. &amp; Lise, A. A. (2015) Taxonomic notes on the crab spider genus Tobias Simon, 1895 (Araneae, Thomisidae, Stephanopinae). Zootaxa, 4034 (3), 565 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4034.3.8" type="journal article">
Machado 
<emphasis box="[542,590,890,915]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">et al</emphasis>
. (2015
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[684,744,891,915]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" refId="ref24473" refString="Machado, M., Teixeira, R. A. &amp; Lise, A. A. (2018) There and back again: more on the taxonomy of the crab spiders genus Epicadus (Thomisidae: Stephanopinae). Zootaxa, 4382 (3), 501 - 530. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4382.3.4" type="journal article">2018</bibRefCitation>
), the difference in color of the pustular setiferous tubercles on the femora I and II allows an easy differentiation between 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mello-LeitÃ £ o" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[853,1071,926,951]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Epicadus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudatus">
